wp create thumbnail "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
===================================================================

NAME
----

wp create thumbnail - **This function was deprecated in [3.5](/Version_3.5 "Version 3.5"). Use

SYNOPSIS
--------

**This function was deprecated in [3.5](/Version_3.5 "Version 3.5"). Use
`wp_get_image_editor()` instead.**

This was once used to create a thumbnail from an Image given a maximum
side size.

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$file` 
:   ([*mixed*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Mixed "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Filename of the original image, Or attachment id.
    Default: *None*

 `$max_side` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Maximum length of a single side for the thumbnail.
    Default: *None*

 `$deprecated` 
:   ([*mixed*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Mixed "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Function was never used
    Default: *None*

RETURN
------

 (string) 
:   Thumbnail path on success, Error string on failure

CHANGE LOG
----------

-   [3.5.0](/Version_3.5 "Version 3.5"): Deprecated in favor of
    `wp_get_image_editor()`
-   Since: [1.2.0](/Version_1.2 "Version 1.2")

